  "prompt": "How do I increase font size in Quora?",
  "response": "To increase the font size on Quora, you have a few options:\n\n1. Browser Zoom:\n- Use Ctrl and + (Windows/Linux)\n- Use Cmd and + (Mac)\n- This zooms the entire page, not just text\n\n2. Browser Settings:\n- Go to browser settings\n- Look for text/font size options\n- Adjust default font size\n\n3. Browser Extensions:\n- Some browser extensions can help adjust website text size\n- Examples: \"Font Size Changer\" or \"Zoom Text Only\"\n\n4. Quora Settings:\n- Unfortunately, Quora doesn't have a direct built-in font size option\n- The platform maintains its own default text size\n\n5. Device Settings:\n- On mobile devices, you can adjust text size in accessibility settings\n- This can affect Quora's display\n\n6. Third-party Apps:\n- Some Quora reading apps might offer font size customization\n\nThe most straightforward methods are browser zoom or browser text size settings. Quora itself doesn't provide a native font size adjustment feature.",
